  "text": "The null hypothesis that both distributions are the same is rejected at the highest level of confidence possible with three sessions for both the RPR and the IPR scheme (p = 0.1088). For the T scheme, the results are not significant, but the direction of the change is correct (p = 1). [CITATION_1] Figure 2 below shows the fraction of subjects whose effort was higher in the LV than in the HV environment (as the theory predicts). At least half the subjects responded to the incentives in the correct direction in each scheme (50% in RPR, 67% in IPR and 61% in the Tournament).",
